   of 0.774, an IBS of 0.090. The F1 score was of 0.945, accuracy was 89.67
   and precision was 90.99\%. The time-dependent ROC analysis produced an
   AUC of 0.709, indicating a moderate predictive performance. Lastly, the
   analysis shows that the three most important variables are donor age,
   BMI, and recipient age.MethodsWe employed a RSF model to analyze a
   simulated dataset of kidney transplant recipients. The data were split
